TITLE: Meta Fields in GraphQL Queries
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the __typename meta field to determine the concrete type returned by a union type field. This is useful when handling different possible return types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/pages/learn/queries.mdx#2025-04-08_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
{
  search(text: "an") {
    __typename
    ... on Human {
      name
    }
    ... on Droid {
      name
    }
    ... on Starship {
      name
    }
  }
}
```

