TITLE: Creating a Minimal 'Hello world' GraphQL Server with Ariadne
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a basic GraphQL server using Ariadne. It defines a simple schema with a 'hello' query, implements a resolver function, and sets up the GraphQL application. The server will respond with 'Hello world!' when the 'hello' query is executed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/code/language-support/python/server/ariadne.md#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from ariadne import ObjectType, gql, make_executable_schema
from ariadne.asgi import GraphQL

type_defs = gql(
    """
    type Query {
        hello: String!
    }
    """
)

query_type = ObjectType("Query")

@query_type.field("hello")
def resolve_hello(*_):
    return "Hello world!"

schema = make_executable_schema(type_defs, query_type)

app = GraphQL(schema, debug=True)
```

