TITLE: Creating a Basic GraphQL Schema and Query in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: A complete example showing how to define a GraphQL schema, create resolvers, and execute a query. It imports the necessary GraphQL.js functions, defines a simple schema with a 'hello' query that returns a String, and sets up a resolver that returns 'Hello world!'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/pages/graphql-js/index.mdx#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var { graphql, buildSchema } = require("graphql")

// Construct a schema, using GraphQL schema language
var schema = buildSchema(`
  type Query {
    hello: String
  }
`)

// The rootValue provides a resolver function for each API endpoint
var rootValue = {
  hello() {
    return "Hello world!"
  }
}

// Run the GraphQL query '{ hello }' and print out the response
graphql({
  schema,
  source: "{ hello }",
  rootValue
}).then(response => {
  console.log(response)
})
```

