TITLE: JavaScript Client Code Using Variables in GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: A JavaScript fetch implementation that calls the GraphQL API using query variables. This approach avoids string concatenation and helps prevent injection attacks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/pages/graphql-js/passing-arguments.mdx#2025-04-08_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var dice = 3
var sides = 6
var query = /* GraphQL */`query RollDice($dice: Int!, $sides: Int) {
  rollDice(numDice: $dice, numSides: $sides)
}`

fetch("/graphql", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    Accept: "application/json",
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    query,
    variables: { dice, sides },
  }),
})
  .then(r => r.json())
  .then(data => console.log("data returned:", data))
```

