TITLE: Creating a Hello World GraphQL API with Graphene
DESCRIPTION: A complete example showing how to define a GraphQL schema with Graphene, including a Query type with a hello field and resolver function. The example demonstrates query execution and data retrieval.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/code/language-support/python/server/graphene.md#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import graphene

class Query(graphene.ObjectType):
  hello = graphene.String(name=graphene.String(default_value="World"))

  def resolve_hello(self, info, name):
    return 'Hello ' + name

schema = graphene.Schema(query=Query)
result = schema.execute('{ hello }')
print(result.data['hello']) # "Hello World"
```

