TITLE: Creating a Simple GraphQL Schema with KGraphQL in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a basic GraphQL schema using KGraphQL. It defines an Article data class, sets up a query resolver, and adds a custom property resolver for the Article type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/code/language-support/java-kotlin-android/server/kgraphql.md#2025-04-08_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
data class Article(val id: Int, val text: String)

fun main() {
    val schema = KGraphQL.schema {
        query("article") {
            resolver { id: Int?, text: String ->
                Article(id ?: -1, text)
            }
        }
        type<Article> {
            property<String>("fullText") {
                resolver { article: Article ->
                    "${article.id}: ${article.text}"
                }
            }
        }
    }

    schema.execute("""
        {
            article(id: 5, text: "Hello World") {
                id
                fullText
            }
        }
    """).let(::println)
}
```

