TITLE: Implementing a Basic GraphQL Server with Agoo in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to set up a minimal GraphQL server using the Agoo library. It defines a simple Query type with a 'hello' resolver, creates a schema, initializes and starts the Agoo server, and loads the GraphQL type definitions. The example shows how to expose a '/graphql' endpoint that responds to queries.
