TITLE: Event Sorting Logic in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Utility code that sorts events into past and upcoming categories based on current date. Uses array reduce method to process event dates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/pages/community/events.mdx#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
export const { pastEvents, upcomingEvents } = events.reduce(
  (acc, event) => {
    const now = new Date()
    const date = new Date(event.date)
    if (date < now) {
      acc.pastEvents.push(event)
    } else {
      acc.upcomingEvents.push(event)
    }
    return acc
  },
  { pastEvents: [], upcomingEvents: [] },
)
```

